WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.500 --> 00:00:04.000
This is the fine-structure constant.

2
00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.200
Physics measures it. TFPT claims it's the unique root of a short equation —

3
00:00:08.200 --> 00:00:11.200
fixed by two inputs, and nothing else.

4
00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:14.800
Big claim. So I'll also show you exactly where it could break.

5
00:00:15.300 --> 00:00:19.200
TFPT isn't another table of nice numbers — it's a discrete compiler.

6
00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:24.000
Two operative inputs go in: a boundary constant, c₃ = 1/(8π),

7
00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.600
and a five-fold carrier, g_car = 5.

8
00:00:27.600 --> 00:00:32.600
From those, one structure is built: the carrier makes the D₅ side,

9
00:00:32.600 --> 00:00:37.000
four marked boundary points make the A₃ family geometry,

10
00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:41.600
and the μ₄ glue closes them into E₈.

11
00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:46.800
And this defuses the usual no-go theorems: E₈ is not a gauge group of nature.

12
00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:50.800
It's the audit hull — the consistency container.

13
00:00:50.800 --> 00:00:55.800
The Standard Model is a readout after projection, not 'everything is E₈.'

14
00:00:56.300 --> 00:01:00.600
What comes out splits cleanly. First, the discrete core —

15
00:01:00.600 --> 00:01:04.000
exact, or machine-checked:

16
00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:09.000
three families, hypercharges, the flavor matrix, sixteen carrier states,

17
00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:13.600
the recurring 2-3-5, the Coxeter number 30, the 240 roots of E₈.

18
00:01:13.600 --> 00:01:18.600
Then the boundary side: from c₃ comes one seed, φ₀ —

19
00:01:18.600 --> 00:01:23.600
and from it: the Cabibbo structure, the electromagnetic fixed point, the scale grammar.

20
00:01:23.600 --> 00:01:29.600
The fine-structure constant lands as the unique positive root of a cubic: 137.0359992 —

21
00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:33.000
1.9 sigma from the measured value.

22
00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:36.800
Not a fit. A forced root.

23
00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:41.000
The Standard-Model part compresses hard.

24
00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:46.000
Masses and mixings don't come from free Yukawa numbers —

25
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:50.600
they come from one texture: a seed, a fixed flavor matrix, integer word-lengths.

26
00:01:50.600 --> 00:01:55.000
The CKM angles and the leading CP phase fall out of the same holonomy;

27
00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:58.000
the reactor angle θ₁₃ comes straight from the seed.

28
00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:02.800
Absolute masses run through one typed bridge, v_geo, and standard RG. Dimensional analysis with a seatbelt.

29
00:02:03.300 --> 00:02:06.600
Now the honest part — how do you kill it?

30
00:02:06.600 --> 00:02:11.600
The predictions were frozen in a blind registry before any comparison — machine-enforced.

31
00:02:11.600 --> 00:02:15.000
sin²θ₁₂ ≈ 0.3067.   sin²θ₁₃ ≈ 0.0231.

32
00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:18.600
α⁻¹ as a fixed point. A small tensor ratio r between 0.0033 and 0.0048.

33
00:02:18.600 --> 00:02:22.000
Normal neutrino ordering, with a low mass floor.

34
00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:27.200
The closed core predictions sit within about one sigma today — every tension tracked in the open.

35
00:02:27.200 --> 00:02:33.600
The near-term kill tests are real: neutrino mass from DESI and CMB-S4, and proton decay at Hyper-Kamiokande.

36
00:02:34.300 --> 00:02:37.600
How is this kept honest?

37
00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:42.600
Every statement carries a status — exact, conditional, open, or kill-test —

38
00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:46.200
in one machine-readable ledger: the single source of truth.

39
00:02:46.200 --> 00:02:52.800
And a red team whose job is to break the theory, not confirm it — or math becomes numerology with better typography.

40
00:02:53.300 --> 00:02:56.600
So what's actually open?

41
00:02:56.600 --> 00:03:00.200
The discrete compiler is structurally closed.

42
00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:05.600
The one hard knot is a single theorem: the raw, reflection-positive seam state must be —

43
00:03:05.600 --> 00:03:09.200
canonically — the holomorphic (E₈)₁ net at τ = i.

44
00:03:09.200 --> 00:03:13.000
Both proof routes meet there. The sharpest remaining piece has a name: Flat-Away.

45
00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:18.000
Close it, and the structural core is done. What stays are deliberately typed interfaces.

